“Never Enough”
Circle: Third Ring — Gluttony
Theme: Consumption without fulfillment • Want vs need • Hollow abundance
Quest Premise
The Gluttony Circle is not loud or chaotic.
It is slow, bloated, and endlessly indulgent.
Food, objects, memories, even emotions lie everywhere—offered freely.
Nothing is locked. Nothing is guarded.
And yet… nothing satisfies.

I. The Banquet of Ash
Objective: Partake to proceed.
The player enters a massive, cathedral-like hall modeled after a ruined basilica:
Long tables stretch endlessly.
Plates refill themselves the moment they’re empty.
The air smells warm and comforting—but wrong.

A disembodied voice murmurs:
“Eat. Take. You’ve earned it.”
Mechanics
The exit is sealed.
The player must interact with offerings to unlock progress.
Each interaction grants a temporary buff (damage, speed, defense).
But:
Each buff also stacks a hidden burden:
Slower stamina regen
Heavier movement
Slight screen distortion
The more the player takes, the harder it becomes to move.

II. The Weight of Want
Objective: Reach the end of the hall.
As the player continues:
Enemies appear—bloated, sluggish, endlessly consuming.

They drop more “offerings” instead of loot.
Key Choice

The player can:
Consume drops to stay strong but grow heavier
Or refuse, making combat harder but movement freer

NPC whispers react dynamically:
If you consume often:
“Good. Don’t stop. You’ll feel better soon.”

If you refuse:
“Why deny yourself? You’re already here.”

III. The Mirror Feast
Objective: Confront yourself.
At the far end, the player finds a massive mirror behind a final table.
When interacted with:

The mirror shows the player as they are now:
Armor strained
Movements sluggish
Or thin, worn, but standing

A single prompt appears:
[Take One More]
[Walk Away]
Outcomes
Take One More
Massive temporary power spike
Screen shakes
The mirror cracks
Walk Away
All buffs fade

The seal opens silently
Either choice opens the path forward—but 
affects:
Boss dialogue
Ring behavior
The Betrayal Counter

Quest Completion
As the player exits, the voice whispers one last time:
“You were full…
so why were you still hungry?”
The path descends toward the Gluttony Boss Arena.




